# Pinned mlsgrid-sync schema contract

The integration tests build their fixture database from mlsgrid-sync's schema
migration, vendored here at a pinned release so the test is a *cross-repo
contract test*: if mlsgrid-sync's schema drifts from what this adapter reads,
refreshing the pin makes the change explicit and reviewable.

    repo         github.com/piotrsenkow/mlsgrid-sync
    tag          v0.1.0
    commit       c5b3c55118eb3906431bab546bb5305c371157eb
    file         internal/store/postgres/migrations/0001_init.sql
    blob sha1    2a5f03f97ca0cd8ee2c11d743a2a05257d729546
    contract     1.0.0 (major asserted by adapters/postgres.ExpectedContractMajor)

## Refreshing the pin

Re-vendor the migration from a newer mlsgrid-sync tag:

    git -C <mlsgrid-sync> show <tag>:internal/store/postgres/migrations/0001_init.sql \
        > adapters/postgres/testdata/contract/0001_init.sql

then update the coordinates above and re-run `make test-integration`. A change
here is a schema-contract event: bump ExpectedContractMajor only on a *major*
contract bump, and update the tools/list golden if result shapes move.

A live drift check runs in CI (the `contract-drift` job, `make verify-pin`):
it re-derives the blob sha1 from the vendored copy and diffs it against the
file fetched from mlsgrid-sync at the commit above, so a moved tag or a
hand-edited vendor fails the build. This file stays the single source of truth
for the pin — the check reads its coordinates.
